data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_EncryptWebConfig
data.value: The server configuration file should be encrypted

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_EncryptWebConfig_Details
data.value: Sensitive information is stored in the server configuration file (appsettings.json). It is recommended to enable encryption to prevent tampering and ensure confidentiality.

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_GatewayTLS
data.value: Devolutions Gateway should be configured to use a secure communication channel (TLS).

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_GatewayTLS_Details
data.value: The Devolutions Gateway should use TLS to provide communication confidentiality and integrity over the network. Otherwise, actions such as authentication and authorization requests could be sent in cleartext over the network, which can be intercepted and read by an attacker. Note also that certain protocols rely on this security layer and may transmit data in an unencrypted format when it is deactivated. In the Devolutions Gateway configuration, check Enable TLS to enable secure communications.

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_HTTPS
data.value: Secure HTTPS communications should be enabled.

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_HTTPS_Details
data.value:
Secure communications guarantee the integrity and confidentiality of the data transmitted between the client and the server.
In Devolutions Server Console â Server Settings â IIS, uncheck "Disable HTTPS".

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_HTTPSDatasource
data.value: HTTPS should be used to connect to the data source

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_InsecureSshAlgorithms

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_InsecureSshKey

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_LDAPS
data.value: Active Directory should be configured to use a secure communication channel

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_LDAPS_Details
data.value:
The LDAPS protocol should be used to provide communication confidentiality and integrity over the network. Otherwise, actions such as password resets could send the password in cleartext over the network.
In Administration â Server Settings â Authentication â Domain, check "Enable LDAPS".

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_MultipleDbAccounts
data.value: Database accounts should be different for web applications, schedulers, and management tools

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_MultipleDbAccounts_Details
data.value:
Minimum privileges should be granted and applied for service and database accounts to operate. Shared and excessively privileged service and database accounts may induce unnecessary security risk exposure.
In Devolutions Server Console â Server Settings â Database â Credentials â Advanced Credentials.

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_NumberOfAdmin
data.value: The administrator count should be no more than five

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_NumberOfAdmin_Details
data.value: Limiting the number of active administrators within the platform will reduce the attack surface for an attacker to only those accounts configured. Having more than 5 administrators can also be a sign of poor segregation of duties within the business unit or organization.

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_NumberOfAdminRole
data.value: Limit the number of Administrator user groups

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_NumberOfAdminRole_Details
data.value: The application should have a limited number of administrator user groups. Having an unnecessarily large amount of highly privileged user groups can increase the risk of a user belonging to one of them being breached. As per the principle of least privilege, users should only have the required permissions to properly complete their work.

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_NumberOfDatabaseUsers
data.value: Existing database users should be migrated to a different authentication type.

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_NumberOfDatabaseUsers_Details
data.value: Existing database users might currently have unauthorized access to your database. Migrating those users to another authentication type will reduce the risks of a malicious actor accessing and manipulating data directly on your database.

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_OktaToken

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_OktaToken_Details

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_PasswordStrengthEngine

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_RDPAuthenticationLevel

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_RefreshTokenLifetime

data.name: SecurityDashboardWeakness_RefreshTokenLifetime_Details

In Administration â Server Settings â Advanced.
